in december 2007 , the fasb issued replacement guidance that requires the acquirer of a business to recognize and measure the identifiable assets acquired , the liabilities assumed , and any non-controlling interest in the acquired entity at fair value .
this replacement guidance also requires transaction costs related to the business combination to be expensed as incurred .
it was effective for business combinations for which the acquisition date was on or after the start of the fiscal year beginning after december 15 , 2008 .
the adoption of this guidance in the first quarter of 2009 did not have any impact on the company 2019s consolidated financial statements .
